<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

{{>head}}

<body>

<main class="home">
  <header class="hero">
    <img src="{{ basePath }}/images/konviw.svg" alt="hero">
    <p class="description">Enterprise public viewer for your Confluence pages</p>
  </header>
  <div class="features">
    <div class="feature">
      <h2>Read-only Confluence pages</h2>
      <p>Page content formated with configurable CSS stylesheets, zoomable images, draw.io diagrams preview, web statistics, code with syntax highlighted, reading progress bar...</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature">
      <h2>Simpler API</h2>
      <p>Simplified REST API providing a read-only access to search pages and retrieve page content.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="feature">
      <h2>Create stunning Presentations on the Web</h2>
      <p>Web slides deck directly from your Confluence pages. Thanks to the awesome job done by reveal.js</p>
    </div>
  </div>
          <div class="center">
          <p>To get started just paste a page ID from your Confluence instance and we will bring you there or read the <a
              href="https://sanofi-iadc.github.io/konviw/">konviw documentation</a>.
          <p><input type="text" id="pageID" class="pageID-input" size="15" placeholder="Type a Page ID">
            <button type="button" onclick="goToPage();" class="goToPage-btn">Go to Page</button>
          </p>
      </div>

